{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Button is a UI element that triggers an action or event, and is used to initiate tasks or confirming an action."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Button appears in different layouts, styles and states to indicate hierarchy or emphasis."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSButton"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Actions"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Appearances","level":2,"anchor":"Appearances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Five appearances are proposed for all layouts:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc. It is a “call for action”."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"brand","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": A brand primary color alternative to the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" button."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To be used sparingly for high-value specific actions or to visually anchor a brand moment. Do not use it as the default primary button in your interfaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Brand"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"minimal","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"negative","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Negative"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Code samples","level":2,"anchor":"Code-samples"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default appearance","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\", appearance: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance and button taking full width","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong, isFullWidth: true) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSButton(LocalizedStringKey(\"validate_button\"), bundle: Bundle.module, appearance: .strong) { }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSButton(text: \"Button\",","               icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","               flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Styles","level":2,"anchor":"Styles"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Two style are available:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for  states "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"disabled","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"pressed","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"hovered","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" or normal (i.e. "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"enabled","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"loading","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Rounded layout","level":2,"anchor":"Rounded-layout"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Buttons can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To activate the rounded button behavior, set to true the ","type":"text"},{"code":"hasRoundedButtons","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Tuning","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like ","type":"text"},{"code":"SoshTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"WireframeTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Colored surface","level":2,"anchor":"Colored-surface"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If button is placed on colored surface using ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrome mode.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative nor a Brand button on a colored surface."}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Specific behavior","level":2,"anchor":"Specific-behavior"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For accessibility reasons, if the system settings for reducing motion is enabled, the loading indicator does not move.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For ecodesign reasons, if the device is in low power mode, the loading indicator does not move.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Design documentation","level":2,"anchor":"Design-documentation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-button","type":"reference"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Themes rendering","level":2,"anchor":"Themes-rendering"},{"type":"heading","text":"Orange","level":3,"anchor":"Orange"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Orange","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Orange Compact","level":3,"anchor":"Orange-Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_OrangeCompact","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Sosh","level":3,"anchor":"Sosh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Sosh","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Wireframe","level":3,"anchor":"Wireframe"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Wireframe","type":"image"}]},{"style":"note","name":"Version","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3.2.0 (Figma component design version)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"style":"note","name":"Since","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.10.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"struct","title":"OUDSButton","roleHeading":"Structure","platforms":[{"introducedAt":"15.0","name":"iOS","depr